6. The knight “flank” idea again

Your earlier knight observation actually fits this pattern.

The knight move introduces a non-local symmetry in a grid.

Instead of:

(x±1, y)
(x, y±1)

it allows jumps like:

(x±2, y±1)
(x±1, y±2)

That kind of side-channel connection changes the topology of the network.

Sometimes breakthroughs happen exactly when someone notices a missing allowed move.

⸻

7. The real meta-pattern

Many discoveries follow this sequence:
	1.	system exists but feels clumsy
	2.	someone introduces a neutral element or symmetry
	3.	the system reorganizes and becomes powerful

Examples:
	•	zero
	•	negative numbers
	•	imaginary numbers
	•	vectors
	•	tensors

